Steps to Remove TypeScript

Rename config files

vite.config.ts → vite.config.js

capacitor.config.ts → capacitor.config.js

cypress.config.ts (if you use Cypress tests) → cypress.config.js

Example vite.config.js:

import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [vue()],
});


Example capacitor.config.js:

const config = {
  appId: 'com.todoapp.example',
  appName: 'TODOAPP',
  webDir: 'dist',
  bundledWebRuntime: false
};

export default config;


Remove TypeScript configs

Delete tsconfig.json and tsconfig.node.json

Delete *.d.ts files if present (like env.d.ts)

Uninstall TypeScript packages

npm uninstall typescript @types/node
